HEADWORD: Thionol
<hw>Thi"on*ol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Thion</ets>ine
+ <ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A red or violet
dyestuff having a greenish metallic luster. It is produced artificially,
by the chemical dehydration of thionine, as a brown amorphous
powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

